import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['normal'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Normal Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperatures?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['normal'], data['actual'])
    plt.title('How does the actual temperature compare to the normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Normal Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Actual Temperature')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('day')['actual'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['actual'])
    plt.title('What is the average actual temperature recorded for each day?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Average Actual Temperature')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(integer=True))
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=90)
    ax.set_xlabel('Day')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')
    ax.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], label='Actual Temperature')
    ax.plot(data['day'], data['normal'], label='Normal Temperature')
    ax.plot(data['forecast'], data['normal'], label='Forecast Temperature')
    plt.title('How accurate are the weather forecasts compared to the actual temperature recorded?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
